    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "A powerful passive that guarantees a critical hit when attacked from behind.",
        "When you get a kill or assist, the cooldowns of all skills are reset, allowing you to aim for consecutive kills.",
        "High surprise attack performance and escape power with ultimate that allows you to enter a stealth state"
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "It has very low durability and will be defeated without being able to do anything if it receives hard CC (control).",
        "Attacks from the front greatly reduce firepower, so careful positioning is required.",
        "It's easy to get isolated in situations where there are multiple healthy enemies or if you can't get the first kill."
      ],
      "playstyle": "As a typical Assassin, you should never charge in first in teamfights. Wait until your allies have engaged and the enemy's powerful CC skills are expended, then use stealth to sneak up on the enemy's rearguard. Take advantage of guaranteed critical hits from behind to reliably take down soft targets, use skill resets to mow down enemies one after another, or use hit-and-away moves to safely escape."
    },
    "meta": {
      "summoner_spells": [
        "punishment"
      ],
      "synergy": [
