      "strengths": [
        "Skill 2 increases the movement speed of all allies and provides a powerful pseudo-heal that recovers part of the damage received.",
        "Ultimate's wide range of silence and slow allows you to activate enemy skills and break formations.",
        "In group battles from the mid-game onward, where cooldown reduction items are available, you can significantly increase the survivability and mobility of your allies."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "Has low influence in early lane battles and small group battles, and is easily pushed by aggressive Support.",
        "Because it relies heavily on the cooperation of allies, it is difficult to demonstrate its true value if allies do not understand the effects of the skill.",
        "Since it cannot act as a wall of flesh like a Tank, it may not be able to directly protect allies from Assassin's burst damage."
      ],
      "playstyle": "In the early stages, use skill 1 to poke and see bushes from a safe distance, and be patient until the entire team grows. From the middle stage onward, always work with your allies and use Skill 2 to help you smoothly enter and exit battles. You will need to use your ultimate silence at the timing when the enemy Assassin rushes in or at key points in a group battle, blocking enemy skill combos and creating an environment where your allies can fight advantageously."
    },
