    "status_text": "Max HP 3325\nMax MP 640\nPhysical attack 171\nMagic attack 10 (0+10)\nPhysical defense 150|20%\nMagic defense 75|11.1%\nMovement speed 365\nPhysical defense penetration 0|0%\nMagic defense penetration 0|0%\nAttack speed bonus 5%\nCritical rate 0%\nCritical effect 200%\nPhysical life steal 0%\nMagic life steal 0%\nCooldown reduction 0%\nAttack range long distance\nResistance 0%\nHP recovery every 5 seconds 43\nMP recovery every 5 seconds 16",
    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "A unique skill set that can deal continuous damage (poison) to enemies and heal allies at the same time.",
        "The longer the battle goes on, the more poison stacks accumulate, and the power of the ultimate's total recovery and large damage increases.",
        "Depending on the build, you can build up magic defense and physical defense, and demonstrate amazing tenacity as a sub-tank and healer."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "The firing range is short, and you need to move forward to apply the skill, so you are likely to get hit.",
        "Since he does not have movement skills (blink) or hard CC, he cannot escape if he is suddenly approached by a highly mobile Assassin.",
        "The instantaneous burst damage is low, and if the composition and coordination of your allies is insufficient, you will be defeated before the poison is fully distributed."
      ],
      "playstyle": "From the beginning to the middle of the game, farm while healing your allies and harassing (poisoning) your enemies without forcing yourself to kill them. In group battles, it is ideal to always take a position slightly behind your ally's vanguard and use your skills to engage both enemies and allies. Be aware of counter tactics that can quickly turn the tide of battle by activating your ultimate with poison stacks (up to 5) accumulated on both enemy and ally."
    },
    "meta": {
      "summoner_spells": [
        "epiphany"
      ],
      "synergy": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Hakuki",
          "reason": "Tanks with high durability fight on the front lines, making it easier to accumulate poison stacks and heal allies.",
          "hero_id": "hero_022"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Nianyu",
          "reason": "Since you can block enemy attacks, you can create an environment that provides sustained recovery and damage.",
          "hero_id": "hero_036"
        }
      ],
      "counters": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Yang Kai",
          "reason": "It is difficult to carry into sustained battles because it inhibits recovery and deals burst damage.",
          "hero_id": "hero_065"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Mai Shiranui",
          "reason": "It has high mobility and burst damage, and will defeat you without giving you a chance to recover.",
          "hero_id": "hero_050"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
