        "Very weak early game due to poor laning and wave clear abilities until he builds his core items.",
        "Low mobility makes him vulnerable to kiting by ranged attackers and highly mobile heroes.",
        "Blind-picking him carries the risk of facing strong 1v1 counter heroes that can dominate the lane."
      ],
      "playstyle": "Since his early game is very weak, avoid forced fights and farm safely under the tower until your core items (defense and attack) are complete. From mid to late game, act as the team's main frontline and attacker. Use your Ultimate to dive into the enemy backline or grouped areas. Maintain the enchanted state (glowing weapon) to continuously deal true damage, fighting as a brawler while enduring attacks with your shield and healing."
    },
    "meta": {
      "summoner_spells": [
        "Flash"
      ],
      "synergy": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Dolia",
          "reason": "She can reset his Ultimate's cooldown, allowing him to jump twice and dominate team fights.",
          "hero_id": "hero_051"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Guiguzi",
          "reason": "Pulls enemies together, ensuring Lu Bu's devastating AoE Ultimate hits multiple targets.",
          "hero_id": "hero_072"
        }
      ],
      "counters": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Marco Polo",
          "reason": "Uses his high mobility to dodge Lu Bu's attacks while safely poking him with true damage from afar.",
          "hero_id": "hero_033"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Zhang Fei",
          "reason": "Can use his skills to knock Lu Bu away the moment he lands from his Ultimate, preventing him from disrupting the formation.",
          "hero_id": "hero_058"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
