    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "It boasts high base damage and combo firepower from the early stages, and has excellent snowball performance.",
        "The mobility of the blink skill and the recovery effect of the ultimate allow you to fight tenaciously.",
        "It has a short cooldown and can frequently rotate skills to intervene in battle."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "He is a typical early game hero, and his influence decreases significantly the longer the match goes on.",
        "If you receive CC while your ultimate is active, it will be interrupted and your low durability will likely be exposed.",
        "It depends on the accuracy of the skill, and if you miss it, you will have no way to escape and will be susceptible to counterattacks."
      ],
      "playstyle": "Mainly used as a jungler (or crash lane), he takes advantage of his overwhelming strength in the early stages and aims to gank and acquire objects from the early stages to take control of the match. Close the distance quickly with blink skills, and use combos that combine passives and skills to take down isolated enemies. You will stall in the late game, so be sure to hold on to the advantage you gained early on and try to settle the match early before your opponent scales up."
    },
