      "strengths": [
        "The passive effect increases the defense power of yourself and the ally with the lowest HP, allowing you to strongly protect your allies.",
        "He has multiple knock-up and damage reduction skills, and is highly capable of controlling group battles.",
        "It has excellent basic survivability as a tank, allowing it to stand on the front lines and withstand attacks."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "Their mobility is low, and if their skills are on cooldown, they are likely to be attacked one-sidedly from a distance.",
        "It doesn't have the firepower to kill enemies, so if your allies don't help you, you'll just become a target.",
        "To engage, you need to rush into the enemy line, and if you get the timing wrong, you will be isolated and defeated."
      ],
      "playstyle": "As a roam support, you will stand close to your ally carries (marksmen and mages) and provide passive defense buffs while preventing enemies from getting close. In mid-game teamfights, use your ultimate to break up enemy lines with a huge knockup, or use it as a powerful peel to protect your allies. The most important role is to always know the location of allied damage dealers and serve as a bulwark so they can safely unleash their firepower."
    },
