    "status_text": "Basic status\nMax HP 3508\nMax energy 90\nPhysical attack 185 (175+10)\nMagic attack 0\nPhysical defense 150|20%\nMagic defense 75|11.1%\nattack status\nMovement speed 380\nPhysical defense penetration 0|0%\nMagic defense penetration 0|0%\nAttack speed bonus 0%\nCritical rate 0%\nCritical effect 200%\nPhysical life steal 0%\nMagic life steal 0%\nCooldown reduction 0%\nAttack range close range\ndefense status\nResistance 0%\nHP recovery every 5 seconds 50\nEnergy recovery every 5 seconds 0",
    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "Very powerful in early lane battles and has an advantage against many facing heroes in Crash Lane.",
        "He has a high HP recovery ability with skills and has excellent sustain that allows him to stay in the lane for a long time.",
        "Skills with accumulated energy have enhanced damage and CC, and exhibit high burst firepower."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "Combat power is highly dependent on the energy gauge, and if you engage in a battle with insufficient energy, you will not be able to demonstrate your true power.",
        "Although it has durability, it is weak to enemy CC chains and is easily incapacitated if its skill combo is interrupted.",
        "It is difficult to get close to highly mobile carries and poke-composed enemies who fight at a distance."
      ],
      "playstyle": "Before starting a battle or group battle, it is essential to fill up your energy gauge by attacking minions and neutral monsters. There will be a big power spike when you reach level 4, so use that strength to roam to other lanes and take control of the entire map. Please flexibly change the balance of firepower items and armor according to the composition of the enemy, and be conscious of how you can reliably capture the enemy carry with energy-enhancing skills."
    },
    "meta": {
      "summoner_spells": [
        "epiphany",
        "execution"
      ],
      "synergy": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Oniyako",
          "reason": "Because stealth and strong pull make it easier for Biron's skills and area damage to hit multiple people.",
          "hero_id": "hero_072"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Liu Bang",
          "reason": "Because you can safely support Biron's forceful dive with the shield and teleport from ult.",
          "hero_id": "hero_043"
        }
      ],
      "counters": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Yumeki",
          "reason": "Biron's strong shield offsets Biron's damage, giving him an advantageous trade in lane battles.",
          "hero_id": "hero_080"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Lu Bu",
          "reason": "This is because the guaranteed damage penetrates Biron's reliable shield and causes great damage.",
          "hero_id": "hero_024"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
