    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "Overwhelming map control with skills that allow you to move while ignoring the terrain",
        "High sustain ability to absorb health from multiple targets",
        "Powerful execution mechanic that instantly kills enemies whose health falls below a certain level"
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "Weak to CC, easily defeated if stopped immediately after engaging",
        "Vulnerable if you receive burst damage before taking advantage of your own recovery or execution",
        "There are many situations where you rely on your allies' sharpening rather than initiating alone."
      ],
      "playstyle": "In the early stages, use your terrain skills to quickly move around the jungle and gank from unpredictable angles to control the pace of the match.In teamfights, instead of jumping in head first, wait for your allies to wear down your enemy's health, or aim for the rear from a blind spot on the flank. The key is to reliably take down enemies that have entered the execution range while maintaining the continuous damage and recovery from medium range with the normal attack Soul Link."
    },
    "passive": {
      "name": "Passive: Soul Resonance",
      "description": "When using a normal attack, the resonance of the sword will link with the enemy's soul for 3 seconds. Soul Chain deals 88% (50% of physical attack) physical damage each time. While the soul chain is connected, the damage frequency will gradually increase, and when it ends, it will deal an additional 211 (70 + 80% of physical attack) magic damage.\n100% special effect is applied to the damage at the beginning and end of Soul Chain, and 40% special effect is applied to all other damage.",
      "table": {
