              "280",
              "320",
              "360",
              "400"
            ]
          },
          {
            "label": "Charge damage",
            "values": [
              "200",
              "240",
              "280",
              "320",
              "360",
              "400"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "icon": "/images/skills/hero_101_skill2.png"
    },
    "skill3": {
      "name": "faint fireflies",
      "tags": [
        "bushes",
        "treatment",
        "damage"
      ],
      "cooldown": "CD: 25 seconds",
      "description": "Summons a \"bush of light\" to the specified location. If activated again within 6 seconds, it will fly to the summoned bush and receive 1 stack of Firefly Power.\n“Thicket of Light”: 1 second after summoning the Thicket of Light, it releases fireflies every second towards 5 nearby heroes. Each firefly deals 100 (100 + 20% of magic attack + 3% of additional maximum HP) magic damage or restores 60 (60 + 10% of magic attack + 1.5% of additional maximum HP) HP to an ally hero. When an enemy unit enters a bush of light, it gains vision of that hero. Fireflies caused by bushes of light will no longer appear when they are about to disappear. After the light bush disappears, it becomes a normal bush for 30 seconds.",
      "table": {
        "headers": [
          "Lv.1",
          "Lv.2",
          "Lv.3"
        ],
        "rows": [
          {
            "label": "cool down",
            "values": [
              "50",
              "45",
              "40"
            ]
          },
          {
            "label": "Basic damage",
            "values": [
              "200",
              "300",
              "400"
            ]
          },
          {
            "label": "team damage",
            "values": [
              "200",
              "300",
              "400"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "icon": "/images/skills/hero_101_skill3.png"
    },
    "status_text": "",
    "strategy": {
      "strengths": [
        "Extremely high single-target and area-recovery ability through fireflies, increasing the survivability of allies.",
        "Possesses quick rotation and excellent survival ability due to movement skills that utilize bushes."
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "You cannot generate your own firepower or receive attacks on the front lines on behalf of your allies.",
        "There are few ways to engage other than recovery, and it is difficult to overturn a situation where allies lack firepower."
      ],
      "playstyle": "It is a support role that is close to the ally's carry (firepower role) and constantly recovers and improves continuous combat ability. Use skill 2 to fly from bush to bush to secure a safe position, and skill 1 to thwart enemy attacks with Knock Up. In group battles, use your ultimate to summon a \"bush of light\" and form a position where you can safely heal all your allies, leading to an advantageous battle situation."
    },
    "meta": {
      "summoner_spells": [
        "Flash",
        "Heal"
      ],
      "synergy": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Luban No. 7",
          "reason": "Continuous recovery and protection can greatly increase the survival rate against the low-mobility, high-firepower Marksman.",
          "hero_id": "hero_009"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Bai Qi",
          "reason": "As Tanks continue to fight on the front lines, their high recovery power can raise their actual durability to the maximum.",
          "hero_id": "hero_022"
        }
      ],
      "counters": [
        {
          "hero_name": "Liang",
          "reason": "This is because his movement is blocked by a powerful restraint skill, making it impossible to utilize his mobility to escape by flying over a wall.",
          "hero_id": "hero_049"
        },
        {
          "hero_name": "Wukong",
          "reason": "Due to the high burst damage, there is a risk of being killed instantly before you can use recovery or escape skills.",
          "hero_id": "hero_055"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "hero_102": {
